Prescribe and adopt guidelines which shall govern its work;

Hold hearings and consultations, receive testimonies and reports pertinent to its specified concerns;

Secure from any department, bureau, office or instrumentality of the government such assistance as may be needed, including technical information, preparation and production of reports and submission of recommendations or plans as it may require, particularly a yearly report of the record or performance of each agrarian reform beneficiary as provided under Section 22 of Republic Act No. 6657, as amended;

Secure from the DAR or the LBP information on the amount of just compensation determined to be paid or which has been paid to any landowner;

Secure from the DAR or the LBP quarterly reports on the disbursement of funds for the agrarian reform program;

